-- Iran Sees Non-Aligned Summit Reducing Isolation, Mehr Reports
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-08-23T06:28:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-23/iran-sees-non-aligned-summit-reducing-isolation-mehr-reports.html
Iran ’s decision to host the Non-
Aligned Movement summit in Tehran next week will reduce its
global isolation and help the country bypass international
sanctions, the state-run Mehr news agency reported, citing
Industries, Mines and Commerce Minister Mehdi Ghazanfari.  “The ministry will offer tours of various industrial
centers to the attendees of the summit to present Iran’s
economic, industrial and mining potential,” Ghazanfari said,
 according to Mehr . “The country will present plans to improve
the export of goods and technical and engineering services
during the meeting,” he said, without providing details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Tehran at 
